I usually don't post neg comments or reviews. But this one really got me. I ordered a vegetarian gluten-free pizza with friends to watch the election and hangout. The pizza arrived on time, but the topping was completely slipped to the side. I could only see the pizza bread. It was disappointing, but I thought I could just fix the issue by calling the place. I've talked with the manager, he was amiable and professional. He offered a fresh pizza, and I accepted the idea. However, we waited good an hr 30 mins. Finally got my pizza, and we were super hungry that I did not notice anything except it was very salty. After 5 mins, I immediately noticed IT WAS NOT GLUTEN FREE. My digestive system is allergic to gluten. The entire night my stomach was upset to the point that I had to go to an ER. If I see a huge bill from the hospital, I will sue this place. I have my evidence ready. Be always careful whatever you do. I understand that you are a busy place. But a min you lose attention, and it could potentially harm someone!

We tried appetizers, gluten-free stuffed pizza, regular stuffed, regular pasta, and the gluten free pasta. Since it’s a small dining area, it was busy when we got there but our server was very attentive and conversation did not seem forced, and she made us feel like we were the only dine in at the moment. The older gentleman, which seemed to be the manager also greeted us and asked us how was everything. Jaky mentioned it was family owned and operated which you could tell by the type of service they offer. When we are back in town we will make sure to stop by!
